Pelosi made the comments in an interview, Saturday at the 'Texas Tribune Festival' in Austin, Texas.
'I couldn't help thinking that if a woman behaved like this, they would call her 'hysterical',' Pelosi said about her reaction to Kavanaugh's testimony to the Senate Committee on Justice on Thursday.
Kavanaugh emmotiond the accusations that he would have abused Dr. Christine Blasey Ford sexually when they were both teenagers.
During his opening statement, Kavanaugh was very emmotioned; sometimes he almost shouted and was particularly upset when he told about his family and his high schooling.
He also strongly condemned the democrats in the committee, calling the accusations against him 'great and coordinated character murder' organized by liberals who were angry that Hillary Clinton lost the presidential election in 2016.
Pelosi stated that she found that Kavanaugh’s testimony proved that he was not fit to serve the Supreme Court because he was full of prejudices against the democrats.
'I think he disqualifies himself with his statements and the way he talks about the Clintons and the Democrats', says Pelosi.
Pelosi protested when she was asked if she would try to impose an impeachment proceedings against Kavanaugh if he were appointed, and the Democrats would get the majority in the House of Deputies.
"I can say this about it; if he doesn't tell the truth in Congress, or against the FBI, he's not only unfit for the Supreme Court, but also for the court where he serves now," said Pelosi.
Kavanaugh is currently a judge at the Court of Justice of the District of Columbia (usually abbreviated D.C.) District Court of Appeal.
Pelosi added that as a democrat, she was concerned that Kavanaugh would speak out against the 'Affordable Care Act or Roe v Wade' (Law for Payable Health Care) because Kavanaugh is known as a conservative judge.
Kavanaugh ignored questions about the revision of certain decisions of the Supreme Court during the confirmatory hearings.
'Don't expect us to stand up cheering if a hysterical, prejudiced person is now appointed in the Supreme Court', says Pelosi.
